ENTRY            A0848   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
SUBENT        A0848001   20260205   20260401   20260401       A131
BIB                 12         31
TITLE      Resonance states of hydrogen nuclei H-4 and H-5
           obtained in transfer reactions with exotic beams.
AUTHOR     (S.I.Sidorchuk, D.D.Bogdanov, A.S.Fomichev,
           M.S.Golovkov, Yu.Ts.Oganessian, A.M.Rodin, R.S.Slepnev,
           S.V.Stepantsov, G.M.Ter-Akopian, R.Wolski,V.A.Gorshkov,
           M.L.Chelnokov, M.G.Itkis, E.M.Kozulin, A.A.Bogatchev,
           N.A.Kondratiev, I.V.Korzyukov, A.A.Korsheninnikov,
           E.Yu.Nikolski, I.Tanihata)
INSTITUTE  (4ZZZDUB,2JPNIPC)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,719,229,2003)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,4ZZZDUB)the U-400M cyclotron of FLNR
           The primary triton beam delivered from the cyclotron
           U-400M and the secondary one of 6He were used.
METHOD     (COINC)
CORRECTION The background contribution to the spectra of H-4,5
           measured with the empty target was found to be
           negligibly small for all three reactions studied.
SAMPLE     Liquid tritium and deuterium of the thickness of
            2.0E+21 cm2 were used as targets.
DETECTOR   (TELES,SCIN) Two telescopes were intended for the
           detection of coincident charged particles.
           41 scintillation modules of the neutron spectrometer
           DEMON were used for the neutron detection in
           experiments carried out with the triton beam.
ERR-ANALYS (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
ADD-RES     Energy spectrum of H-5 measured in the reaction
           H-3(t,p)H-5
           Energy spectrum of H-5 measured in the reaction
           H-2(2-He-6,He3)H-5 on reported on fig.4.
HISTORY    (20100401C) SB
           (20260205A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
ENDBIB              31
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           34
